WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:14.908 --> 00:00:17.661
<i>Potential juror number
17. please state your name.</i>

3
00:00:17.744 --> 00:00:19.495
<i>Richard Day.</i>

4
00:00:20.538 --> 00:00:23.624
<i>Can you state for the court
any preexisting opinion. any at all.</i>

5
00:00:23.708 --> 00:00:25.960
<i>that you may hold for the
defendant. Frank Castle?</i>

6
00:00:26.044 --> 00:00:29.172
You mean the Punisher? I
think he's an animal...

7
00:00:29.255 --> 00:00:31.841
a sick. twisted. venal...

8
00:00:31.925 --> 00:00:34.427
Hero. That's what we
should be calling him.

9
00:00:34.510 --> 00:00:36.763
Doing the things the cops won't
do. Frank Castle is a...

10
00:00:36.846 --> 00:00:39.140
A grotesque insult to
the Second Amendment.

11
00:00:39.223 --> 00:00:42.268
a fascist without the authority.
If you ask me.

12
00:00:42.351 --> 00:00:43.937
people like Frank Castle ought to be...

13
00:00:44.020 --> 00:00:46.397
Applauded for putting all the thieves

14
00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:49.108
and muggers and rapists in the
morgue. where they belong.

15
00:00:49.192 --> 00:00:54.405
<i>Let those bastards feel scared walking
down the street for a change.</i>

16
00:01:12.173 --> 00:01:13.842
It's Son of Sam all over again.

17
00:01:13.925 --> 00:01:15.051
It's Bernie Goetz...

18
00:01:15.134 --> 00:01:17.014
It's like the only thing
protecting us is Frank.

19
00:01:17.095 --> 00:01:19.806
I just moved my family to New
York. and now we're moving out.

20
00:01:19.889 --> 00:01:23.893
If anyone can kill anyone in this town...
where does the insanity end?

21
00:01:40.869 --> 00:01:45.289
Counselors. over 400 potential jurors
have come through this courtroom.

22
00:01:45.373 --> 00:01:46.582
So I should tell you.

23
00:01:46.665 --> 00:01:50.795
if you can't agree to move forward
with the 12 men and women selected.

24
00:01:50.879 --> 00:01:53.965
I will make this trial a
living hell for all of you.

25
00:01:54.048 --> 00:01:57.301
Your Honor. New York hasn't seen a trial
this divisive and this public in years.

26
00:01:57.385 --> 00:01:59.846
Finding an impartial jury is not easy.

27
00:01:59.929 --> 00:02:02.140
Everybody has an opinion
about Frank Castle.

28
00:02:02.223 --> 00:02:06.853
It's New York. Mr. Nelson. Everybody
has an opinion about everything.

29
00:02:06.936 --> 00:02:11.024
Ms. Reyes. is the prosecution
satisfied with its jury panel?

30
00:02:11.107 --> 00:02:13.985
- Yes. Your Honor.
- And the defense. Mr. Nelson?

31
00:02:17.030 --> 00:02:20.699
- Uh. yes. Your Honor. we are.
- Thank Christ.

32
00:02:22.701 --> 00:02:25.789
The trial of <i>The People
of New York v. Frank Castle</i>

33
00:02:25.872 --> 00:02:27.665
is now in session.

34
00:04:03.177 --> 00:04:07.223
If I get my hands on the worthless
intern who organized these files...

35
00:04:07.306 --> 00:04:10.018
Oh. I'm sure that intern's just
following the DA's orders.

36
00:04:10.101 --> 00:04:11.560
It's not officially sabotage.

37
00:04:11.644 --> 00:04:14.480
- just sets it back.
- It's a cheap trick.

38
00:04:14.563 --> 00:04:18.401
We got bigger problems.
Like. locking a defense.

39
00:04:18.484 --> 00:04:21.237
- M'Naghten Rule's still our best bet.
- What's that?

40
00:04:21.320 --> 00:04:24.698
- Uh. the. uh. insanity plea.
- Whoa. whoa. guys...

41
00:04:24.782 --> 00:04:26.825
We need to buy a "not guilty" verdict.

42
00:04:26.910 --> 00:04:28.870
My high school debate team could
prove that Castle did it.

43
00:04:28.953 --> 00:04:30.288
We need an affirmative defense.

44
00:04:30.371 --> 00:04:33.082
Yeah. yeah. I get that. but I'm
not so sure Frank is insane.

45
00:04:33.832 --> 00:04:37.211
I'm no doctor. but I'd say he's
at least driven past Crazy Town.

46
00:04:37.295 --> 00:04:38.880
- Foggy. I'm serious.
- She has a point.

47
00:04:38.963 --> 00:04:42.466
I mean. insanity only has a 0.12%
acquittal rate in New York.

48
00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:44.677
Reyes is just gonna call in

49
00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:47.221
some expert shrink witness
to blow our case apart.

50
00:04:47.305 --> 00:04:49.723
- What case?
- Look. what if we...

51
00:04:49.807 --> 00:04:52.685
push for a mistrial?
We get more time.

52
00:04:52.768 --> 00:04:54.896
We talk about the DNR and the
suits and Reyes' involvement.

53
00:04:54.979 --> 00:04:57.065
We get her kicked off the case.

54
00:04:57.148 --> 00:04:58.816
She wouldn't see it coming.

55
00:04:58.900 --> 00:05:02.946
If we go down that road now.
we gotta prove. in a court of law.

56
00:05:03.029 --> 00:05:06.449
that the government willfully hid
evidence of the Punisher ambush.

57
00:05:06.532 --> 00:05:08.034
and that Reyes was involved.

58
00:05:08.117 --> 00:05:11.370
- Well. I was there and you were there.
- We're not exactly impartial. okay?

59
00:05:11.454 --> 00:05:13.957
And either way. we need an
opening statement tomorrow.

60
00:05:14.040 --> 00:05:16.500
I can open with PTSD as
a mitigating factor.

61
00:05:16.584 --> 00:05:17.876
focus on Castle's time at war.

62
00:05:17.961 --> 00:05:20.046
So you think the war is
what made Frank what he is?

63
00:05:20.129 --> 00:05:22.756
Our only goal is to reduce the
charges and set precedent.

64
00:05:22.840 --> 00:05:24.508
Castle made a lot of enemies. all right?

65
00:05:24.592 --> 00:05:26.552
If he goes into general
population. he's as good as dead.

66
00:05:26.635 --> 00:05:29.472
We need to get him somewhere safe.
where he can get help. and...

67
00:05:29.555 --> 00:05:30.595
citing PTSD could do that.

68
00:05:30.639 --> 00:05:33.684
I mean. none of us know
what Castle saw over there...

69
00:05:33.767 --> 00:05:39.148
but research suggests that... PTSD
can be triggered by new stressors.

70
00:05:39.232 --> 00:05:40.566
Like losing your family.

71
00:05:40.649 --> 00:05:42.110
I need to get to work on
the opening statement.

72
00:05:42.193 --> 00:05:44.237
but we need to be sure Castle
will get on board with this.

73
00:05:44.320 --> 00:05:45.904
Uh. I'll try.

74
00:05:45.989 --> 00:05:48.657
I mean. Frank made it pretty clear
he's willing to talk to me. at least.

75
00:05:48.741 --> 00:05:50.326
just as long as I'm alone.

76
00:05:50.409 --> 00:05:54.122
- Are you sure you wanna do that?
- Well. I wanna help.

77
00:05:54.205 --> 00:05:56.624
We have a better shot at
getting him to talk if I go.

78
00:05:57.541 --> 00:06:00.003
I'll grab the list of questions
I was working on.

79
00:06:00.794 --> 00:06:02.005
Okay.

80
00:06:04.882 --> 00:06:06.050
Karen...

81
00:06:07.468 --> 00:06:10.679
You know you don't have
to do this by yourself.

82
00:06:10.763 --> 00:06:13.266
It's okay. Castle doesn't scare me.

83
00:06:14.308 --> 00:06:17.895
- Maybe he should.
- I can take care of myself.

84
00:06:18.896 --> 00:06:22.441
I know... but
I'd be saying it to Foggy.

85
00:06:22.525 --> 00:06:24.777
Or a Navy SEAL.

86
00:06:27.696 --> 00:06:28.906
Just watch your back.

87
00:06:32.410 --> 00:06:33.619
Promise.

88
00:06:35.204 --> 00:06:37.706
Here you go. Just do me
a favor. stick to the script.

89
00:06:37.790 --> 00:06:38.791
Okay.

90
00:06:40.168 --> 00:06:43.129
- Wish me luck.
- Good luck.

91
00:06:45.756 --> 00:06:48.509
Grow up so fast. don't they?

92
00:07:55.284 --> 00:07:58.412
- Hi. Frank.
- Ma'am.

93
00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:11.467
Um. we've been. uh. looking
over similar cases...

94
00:08:11.550 --> 00:08:12.801
legal precedents. and. uh...

95
00:08:12.885 --> 00:08:16.472
we... we think it would help to bring
forth someone from your past...

96
00:08:16.555 --> 00:08:20.017
maybe from your... your military
unit. someone who could. uh...

97
00:08:20.101 --> 00:08:21.810
speak to the nature of your service.

98
00:08:21.894 --> 00:08:26.232
- What's that got to do with anything?
- Um... it's a character witness.

99
00:08:27.816 --> 00:08:30.486
Uh. we put someone on the stand who...
who knows you well.

100
00:08:30.569 --> 00:08:32.530
Uh. can... can speak to
what you've been through.

101
00:08:32.613 --> 00:08:34.698
PTSD. huh?

102
00:08:35.866 --> 00:08:37.786
We think it would
greatly help with your defense.

103
00:08:37.868 --> 00:08:40.788
Don't do that. It's an insult.

104
00:08:41.539 --> 00:08:43.332
Lots of veterans experience it.

105
00:08:43.416 --> 00:08:45.000
I'm not talking about me.
I'm talking about them.

106
00:08:45.083 --> 00:08:47.920
It's an insult to them. people who
are actually going through it.

107
00:08:48.003 --> 00:08:51.382
I know what you wanna do. you
wanna sit here and label me

108
00:08:51.465 --> 00:08:55.261
just another case of some crazy-ass
combat vet who lost his mind. huh?

109
00:08:55.344 --> 00:08:59.140
Maybe that'll appeal to some shitbag
jury in some shitbag court.

110
00:09:01.267 --> 00:09:03.394
It wasn't on a battlefield.

111
00:09:04.978 --> 00:09:07.440
That's not when my life went to shit.

112
00:09:09.150 --> 00:09:11.777
Now. ma'am. I believe that you told me
that you were gonna find me answers.

113
00:09:11.860 --> 00:09:13.821
That's what you said to me. Do
you have anything for me or not?

114
00:09:13.904 --> 00:09:15.072
- Not that easy.
- That what you want?

115
00:09:15.156 --> 00:09:17.200
- You want things to be easy?
- You are on trial

116
00:09:17.283 --> 00:09:20.286
for multiple homicides and you don't
have a defense strategy in place.

117
00:09:20.369 --> 00:09:23.164
You don't cooperate with us.

118
00:09:23.247 --> 00:09:25.666
it doesn't matter if I help you
figure out who killed your family.

119
00:09:25.749 --> 00:09:27.042
you will never see justice.

120
00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:32.840
All you will do. the rest of your
life. is rot in a goddamn jail cell!

121
00:09:41.890 --> 00:09:44.935
Colonel Ray Schoonover. My old CO.

122
00:09:47.062 --> 00:09:50.233
Let's forget the PTSD defense. but
if you want a character witness.

123
00:09:50.316 --> 00:09:51.817
the colonel. he will do.

124
00:09:53.194 --> 00:09:54.195
Thank you.

125
00:09:54.278 --> 00:09:57.114
Now. ma'am. do you have
anything for me or not?

126
00:09:58.199 --> 00:10:02.703
Maybe I just ought to go back and
rot in my goddamn jail cell?

127
00:10:03.954 --> 00:10:06.874
Yeah. Yeah. I did some digging.

128
00:10:07.875 --> 00:10:10.503
All right. there are huge moving parts
and they do not want to be seen.

129
00:10:10.586 --> 00:10:13.339
I've already looked at all of those.
I've done it a hundred times.

130
00:10:13.422 --> 00:10:15.132
Sure...

131
00:10:15.216 --> 00:10:16.634
but you haven't done it with me.

132
00:10:26.685 --> 00:10:28.562
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury.

133
00:10:28.646 --> 00:10:31.774
Imagine. if you will...

134
00:10:33.651 --> 00:10:36.404
Yeah. this is Matt.

135
00:10:36.487 --> 00:10:39.532
- <i>I found a lead.</i>
- Hold on.

136
00:10:47.039 --> 00:10:48.332
Elektra. I can't do this right now.

137
00:10:48.416 --> 00:10:50.668
<i>The guy who encoded that ledger of ours?</i>

138
00:10:50.751 --> 00:10:52.795
<i>Some pervy NYU professor.</i>

139
00:10:52.878 --> 00:10:55.548
<i>master cryptographer who
teaches Asian studies.</i>

140
00:10:55.631 --> 00:10:57.966
<i>I'm gonna go beat the cipher out of him.</i>

141
00:10:58.050 --> 00:10:59.343
- Yeah.
<i>- You wanna come?</i>

142
00:10:59.427 --> 00:11:00.636
- Hey.
- Hey.

143
00:11:00.719 --> 00:11:02.388
You check out these Dogs of Hell depos?

144
00:11:02.471 --> 00:11:03.514
Might as well have been
written in crayon.

145
00:11:03.597 --> 00:11:04.890
I think we could poke
some holes in these.

146
00:11:04.973 --> 00:11:06.813
That's great. Yeah. Just.
uh. give me a minute.

147
00:11:15.359 --> 00:11:17.736
The most important case we've ever
handled starts in the morning.

148
00:11:17.820 --> 00:11:19.154
I can't go with you.

149
00:11:19.237 --> 00:11:20.948
<i>- Can't or won't?</i>
- Can't.

150
00:11:21.031 --> 00:11:23.451
My life doesn't stop
every time you call.

151
00:11:23.534 --> 00:11:26.244
<i>This may be our one chance
to translate this ledger</i>

152
00:11:26.329 --> 00:11:30.333
<i>before the Yakuza adjust their plans and
we lose all the progress we've made.</i>

153
00:11:30.416 --> 00:11:31.584
You're infuriating.

154
00:11:31.667 --> 00:11:34.294
<i>Tell me in person. Two hours.
Barclay and Church.</i>

155
00:11:34.378 --> 00:11:37.423
I know I'm into some sick
shit. but next time. I swear.

156
00:11:37.506 --> 00:11:41.385
all I wanna do is eat moo goo
gai pan off your bodies.

157
00:11:41.469 --> 00:11:44.763
All day.

158
00:11:44.847 --> 00:11:48.642
- We're not Chinese.
- Whatever. it's all hot to me.

159
00:11:49.852 --> 00:11:51.395
What?

160
00:11:51.479 --> 00:11:53.689
He's a repulsive asshole.

161
00:11:53.772 --> 00:11:57.735
A repulsive
asshole who pays well.

162
00:11:58.902 --> 00:12:03.366
I can't tell any of you
apart. but I guarantee...

163
00:12:03.449 --> 00:12:07.370
I know all your tongues
better than you do.

164
00:12:07.453 --> 00:12:10.330
So... be nice.

165
00:12:11.915 --> 00:12:13.250
Get out.

166
00:12:29.892 --> 00:12:32.310
Hey. honey. I'm home.

167
00:12:32.395 --> 00:12:35.481
And you've been awfully naughty.

168
00:12:39.693 --> 00:12:41.654
You're gonna wanna stay real still.

169
00:12:54.207 --> 00:12:55.793
What the hell do you want from me?

170
00:12:55.876 --> 00:12:58.879
- You were hired by the Yakuza.
- I don't know what you're talking about.

171
00:12:58.962 --> 00:13:00.964
You encrypted files for them.

172
00:13:01.048 --> 00:13:03.008
Money must be good.

173
00:13:03.091 --> 00:13:05.928
Not many professors can afford
garish. high-rise flats

174
00:13:06.011 --> 00:13:08.431
and a revolving door of prostitutes.

175
00:13:08.514 --> 00:13:09.807
What do you want me to do?

176
00:13:09.890 --> 00:13:13.811
What you do best. Philip. Translate.

177
00:13:13.894 --> 00:13:14.937
But this time for us.

178
00:13:15.020 --> 00:13:18.231
They will kill me
if I tell you anything.

179
00:13:18.315 --> 00:13:20.635
And if you don't.
we'll make you beg for killing.

180
00:13:29.284 --> 00:13:30.994
Thirty stories up. Philip.

181
00:13:31.078 --> 00:13:33.080
You'd make a mighty good mess.

182
00:13:33.163 --> 00:13:35.499
More liquid than solid. I'd imagine.

183
00:13:36.667 --> 00:13:38.836
- What do you say. Professor?
- Come on. please...

184
00:13:40.253 --> 00:13:41.338
Please... please.

185
00:13:41.421 --> 00:13:43.221
- I'll pay you. I'll do anything.
- Once more.

186
00:13:45.509 --> 00:13:47.553
I can't. I can't. they'll kill me.

187
00:13:47.636 --> 00:13:49.680
It's gonna break.

188
00:13:49.763 --> 00:13:51.098
Okay! Okay. shit!

189
00:13:51.181 --> 00:13:53.016
Stop! I'll do it! I'll do it!

190
00:13:53.100 --> 00:13:54.142
I'll help you.

191
00:14:03.235 --> 00:14:06.780
All right. be a pet and
tell us how to read this last page.

192
00:14:09.407 --> 00:14:11.118
They wanted a code
that couldn't be hacked.

193
00:14:15.664 --> 00:14:18.375
I Put the Japanese alphabet...

194
00:14:18.459 --> 00:14:20.168
through a cipher.

195
00:14:21.419 --> 00:14:23.005
Now...

196
00:14:23.088 --> 00:14:27.009
put the characters through the
matrix. you can decode it all.

197
00:14:27.092 --> 00:14:28.552
You do it.

198
00:14:38.436 --> 00:14:41.023
There's weekly shipments.

199
00:14:41.106 --> 00:14:43.484
Next one is tonight at 11:00.

200
00:14:44.442 --> 00:14:46.695
Bay Ridge Rail Yard.

201
00:14:46.779 --> 00:14:49.114
You find a boxcar with that number...

202
00:14:50.407 --> 00:14:52.868
and you can find the train
you're looking for.

203
00:14:52.951 --> 00:14:54.351
What are they shipping?

204
00:14:55.037 --> 00:14:56.246
It doesn't say. I swear.

205
00:14:56.329 --> 00:14:58.791
I swear! I
can't help you anymore.

206
00:15:02.961 --> 00:15:06.173
Well. thank you
for your help. Professor.

207
00:15:07.800 --> 00:15:11.094
Do yourself a favor. Find
better business partners.

208
00:15:11.929 --> 00:15:13.289
And kill your decorator.

209
00:15:34.743 --> 00:15:37.287
Hey. Hungry?

210
00:15:37.370 --> 00:15:40.666
No. I don't think
I'm ever gonna eat again.

211
00:15:41.709 --> 00:15:43.544
Cost of looking at these all day.

212
00:15:43.627 --> 00:15:46.421
Yeah. How about some fresh coffee?

213
00:15:46.504 --> 00:15:48.256
Yes.

214
00:15:51.885 --> 00:15:53.679
Uh. where's Matt?

215
00:15:53.762 --> 00:15:56.306
I thought he'd be burning
the midnight oil with you.

216
00:15:56.389 --> 00:15:59.017
I... He's. um...

217
00:15:59.101 --> 00:16:01.353
He's working on his opening statements.

218
00:16:01.937 --> 00:16:03.105
Oh.

219
00:16:04.189 --> 00:16:06.441
Did you... you talk to Castle?

220
00:16:08.026 --> 00:16:09.570
Yeah. um...

221
00:16:11.363 --> 00:16:14.950
He. uh. won't endorse PTSD. so...

222
00:16:15.033 --> 00:16:16.744
Oh. shit!

223
00:16:16.827 --> 00:16:19.204
He's... he's not having
war flashbacks. Foggy.

224
00:16:19.287 --> 00:16:20.581
It... it's just not the truth.

225
00:16:20.664 --> 00:16:23.541
Did Castle say anything that we can use?

226
00:16:23.626 --> 00:16:25.543
'Cause when the judge calls
his first witness tomorrow.

227
00:16:25.628 --> 00:16:29.047
my only plan so far is
to run away. and...

228
00:16:29.131 --> 00:16:30.966
open a butcher shop.

229
00:16:31.049 --> 00:16:35.012
Well... I. uh. went over some
of our files with Frank.

230
00:16:35.095 --> 00:16:37.598
The medical examiner's report
from his family's murder.

231
00:16:37.681 --> 00:16:38.849
it's filled out by a. um...

232
00:16:39.767 --> 00:16:41.977
- Dr. Gregory Tepper.
- Yeah.

233
00:16:42.060 --> 00:16:43.896
He's the chief medical examiner.

234
00:16:44.813 --> 00:16:46.189
He's scheduled to testify for Reyes.

235
00:16:46.273 --> 00:16:51.528
Well... his report says that
Lisa. Frank. Jr. and Maria Castle

236
00:16:51.612 --> 00:16:55.741
each were killed by a single gunshot. but
Frank says there were multiple wounds.

237
00:16:55.824 --> 00:16:58.869
He describes them in awful detail. um...

238
00:16:59.870 --> 00:17:01.664
different angles. uh...

239
00:17:01.747 --> 00:17:04.541
bullet calibers. exit wounds
that are too big for a handgun.

240
00:17:04.625 --> 00:17:07.628
I mean. his family was
practically shredded.

241
00:17:07.711 --> 00:17:11.757
There's a discrepancy.
which is good. but...

242
00:17:11.840 --> 00:17:15.969
it's still their word against Frank's.
who was also shot in the head.

243
00:17:16.053 --> 00:17:17.054
Okay.

244
00:17:18.513 --> 00:17:19.973
Just for a minute...

245
00:17:21.016 --> 00:17:24.061
try... try to be Frank Castle.

246
00:17:24.853 --> 00:17:26.772
To be solely fueled by...

247
00:17:26.855 --> 00:17:30.150
by a
single cluster of seconds.

248
00:17:31.902 --> 00:17:34.738
One moment in... in your entire life...

249
00:17:38.033 --> 00:17:41.203
And every time you close your
eyes. you relive that moment.

250
00:17:42.996 --> 00:17:45.248
And every time you open
them. you find only the...

251
00:17:45.332 --> 00:17:50.253
the briefest peace before you realize
that that nightmare is real.

252
00:17:51.714 --> 00:17:53.631
That nothing has changed.

253
00:17:55.425 --> 00:17:57.552
Your family isn't coming back.

254
00:17:58.721 --> 00:18:00.973
And so you watch them die...

255
00:18:01.974 --> 00:18:04.267
all over again right in front of you.

256
00:18:05.185 --> 00:18:08.480
We're not talking about something
that happened to Frank Castle.

257
00:18:08.563 --> 00:18:11.524
we're talking about something
that is happening to him.

258
00:18:14.778 --> 00:18:16.196
I hear you.

259
00:18:17.447 --> 00:18:18.866
But...

260
00:18:18.949 --> 00:18:22.160
short of having his
family's bodies exhumed...

261
00:18:23.704 --> 00:18:26.957
we still have no proof that what
Frank is saying is the truth.

262
00:18:29.918 --> 00:18:32.045
Okay. so...

263
00:18:33.671 --> 00:18:36.925
Let's say the ME's report...
was doctored.

264
00:18:37.009 --> 00:18:40.345
It's still tangential and.
so far. inadmissible.

265
00:18:43.473 --> 00:18:44.808
What?

266
00:18:44.892 --> 00:18:48.729
Unless we can get this ME to corroborate
Frank's story on the stand.

267
00:18:49.772 --> 00:18:51.356
Can you do that?

268
00:18:51.439 --> 00:18:55.152
It's a long shot. He's still
probably in her pocket. but...

269
00:18:56.153 --> 00:18:57.154
if it works...

270
00:18:58.238 --> 00:18:59.740
maybe we expose Reyes

271
00:18:59.823 --> 00:19:01.784
and we get the mistrial
you've been praying for.

272
00:19:01.867 --> 00:19:05.829
So. trial
starts in a few hours.

273
00:19:05.913 --> 00:19:07.748
and in lieu of a bullet-damaged brain.

274
00:19:07.831 --> 00:19:12.002
our case hinges on getting
a dirty medical examiner

275
00:19:12.085 --> 00:19:13.420
to crack on the stand.

276
00:19:14.922 --> 00:19:17.758
Guess I'll call Matt. Give him the news.

277
00:19:17.841 --> 00:19:18.967
Oh. I'll do it.

278
00:19:19.051 --> 00:19:22.304
As long as he has the opening
statement of the year. I'd...

279
00:19:23.680 --> 00:19:25.682
I think maybe we have a chance.

280
00:19:31.021 --> 00:19:34.732
We should make bets on
what the Yakuza are exporting.

281
00:19:34.817 --> 00:19:37.402
Hundred bucks says exotic animals...

282
00:19:37.485 --> 00:19:39.988
or counterfeit purses.

283
00:19:40.072 --> 00:19:42.407
Last time these guys
brought something into town.

284
00:19:42.490 --> 00:19:45.327
it was a cargo ship transporting a kid.

285
00:19:45.410 --> 00:19:47.788
- Human trafficking?
- Yeah. something like that.

286
00:19:55.045 --> 00:19:56.880
- Oh...
- Elektra.

287
00:19:58.298 --> 00:20:00.342
All these cars are empty.
This one's full.

288
00:20:01.259 --> 00:20:03.053
So are the others beyond it.

289
00:20:03.136 --> 00:20:05.806
- Full of what?
- I don't know.

290
00:20:05.889 --> 00:20:07.724
There's no negative space.

291
00:20:07.808 --> 00:20:10.268
Cargo is uniform. There's no real shape.

292
00:20:10.352 --> 00:20:12.645
There's a lot of it. though.

293
00:20:12.729 --> 00:20:14.564
Enough to buckle the tracks.

294
00:20:15.315 --> 00:20:18.276
You're right. This is ours.

295
00:20:18.360 --> 00:20:20.445
Come on. let's go. Let's have a look.

296
00:20:40.465 --> 00:20:42.675
- Dirt.
- Do they know we're here?

297
00:20:43.760 --> 00:20:44.845
Is this a decoy?

298
00:20:47.764 --> 00:20:48.891
Wait.

299
00:20:50.225 --> 00:20:53.186
- They're coming.
- Let's go.

300
00:22:30.325 --> 00:22:32.202
You okay?

301
00:22:33.203 --> 00:22:35.705
The best things in life leave
you breathless. right?

302
00:22:36.373 --> 00:22:40.418
I'm glad you feel that way.
'cause I got something for ya.

303
00:23:27.924 --> 00:23:29.926
It's your lucky day.

304
00:23:32.595 --> 00:23:33.596
Ahh!

305
00:24:03.793 --> 00:24:06.463
What the
hell took you so long?

306
00:24:11.968 --> 00:24:13.470
You hurt?

307
00:24:17.890 --> 00:24:19.476
Let me see.

308
00:24:21.018 --> 00:24:22.104
Ow.

309
00:24:26.399 --> 00:24:28.318
Do you think
this one will scar?

310
00:24:28.401 --> 00:24:30.320
Don't they all?

311
00:24:31.988 --> 00:24:34.157
I suppose I'll never
have short hair again.

312
00:24:34.241 --> 00:24:37.327
Well. you could always tell people
you got it fighting the Yakuza.

313
00:24:38.870 --> 00:24:40.622
No one would believe you anyway.

314
00:24:46.794 --> 00:24:48.921
- All right.
- Thank you.

315
00:24:51.633 --> 00:24:54.969
We make a good team. Matthew.

316
00:24:57.013 --> 00:24:58.431
Keep some pressure on it.

317
00:25:03.853 --> 00:25:05.480
What do you tell people?

318
00:25:06.606 --> 00:25:07.690
About?

319
00:25:09.234 --> 00:25:10.902
Where you got your scars?

320
00:25:14.864 --> 00:25:17.200
Um...

321
00:25:17.284 --> 00:25:19.286
Lucky me. I wear suits to work. so...

322
00:25:20.287 --> 00:25:21.496
rarely comes up.

323
00:25:22.705 --> 00:25:25.292
What do you tell the
women you bring home?

324
00:25:25.375 --> 00:25:27.419
Well. they're enjoying
themselves too much.

325
00:25:27.502 --> 00:25:29.504
They don't ask.

326
00:25:29.587 --> 00:25:30.713
Sure.

327
00:25:34.509 --> 00:25:35.510
Oh. hey.

328
00:25:36.428 --> 00:25:39.264
- You're bleeding.
- Oh.

329
00:25:46.188 --> 00:25:49.482
- That okay?
- It takes a lot more to hurt me.

330
00:25:52.319 --> 00:25:55.071
You. on the other hand...

331
00:26:05.957 --> 00:26:09.168
Oh... I haven't seen this one.

332
00:26:10.962 --> 00:26:13.172
Yeah. the Russians like their knives.

333
00:26:14.216 --> 00:26:16.092
At least. I think it was the Russians.

334
00:26:17.594 --> 00:26:19.095
And these?

335
00:26:20.638 --> 00:26:21.889
The Yakuza.

336
00:26:24.016 --> 00:26:26.143
Actually. a ninja named Nobu.

337
00:26:27.312 --> 00:26:29.231
Nobu Yoshioka?

338
00:26:29.314 --> 00:26:30.940
What. you know him?

339
00:26:31.023 --> 00:26:32.900
By reputation.

340
00:26:35.111 --> 00:26:38.114
Yeah. this was him. too. That hurt.

341
00:26:39.156 --> 00:26:41.993
And the. uh. two on my back.

342
00:26:48.207 --> 00:26:50.084
Wasn't there in college.

343
00:26:50.167 --> 00:26:52.379
Most of them weren't.

344
00:26:54.339 --> 00:26:55.590
You've been busy. huh?

345
00:26:56.299 --> 00:26:57.842
Seems we both have.

346
00:27:09.145 --> 00:27:10.813
Where did you go. Elektra?

347
00:27:13.775 --> 00:27:15.443
The last time we were together...

348
00:27:20.448 --> 00:27:22.867
As far from you as I could.

349
00:27:24.702 --> 00:27:29.081
And... did you find whatever...

350
00:27:30.124 --> 00:27:32.209
you were looking for?

351
00:27:33.836 --> 00:27:37.006
Mostly I found that I was alone.

352
00:27:38.550 --> 00:27:40.802
Then why didn't you come back?

353
00:27:42.470 --> 00:27:45.097
Because you
don't know what I know.

354
00:27:50.102 --> 00:27:51.854
Because you deserve better.

355
00:28:09.664 --> 00:28:11.333
Lie down. Get some rest.

356
00:29:30.953 --> 00:29:34.416
I'm. uh... I'm really late.

357
00:29:34.499 --> 00:29:39.546
I... I will look into the exports.
see where they're coming from.

358
00:29:39.629 --> 00:29:41.548
Yeah.

359
00:29:43.257 --> 00:29:45.885
Have a good day in court. Matthew.

360
00:29:55.645 --> 00:29:56.896
Today. of all days...

361
00:29:57.939 --> 00:29:59.899
I mean. he said he'd be late.
but this is ridiculous.

362
00:29:59.982 --> 00:30:02.109
Foggy. what
is going on with him?

363
00:30:03.069 --> 00:30:06.197
All rise. Court is now in session.

364
00:30:06.280 --> 00:30:09.366
the Honorable Judge
Cynthia Batzer presiding.

365
00:30:09.451 --> 00:30:16.332
Indictment number 1986-4447.
<i>The People v. Frank Castle.</i>

366
00:30:16.416 --> 00:30:17.875
Be seated.

367
00:30:21.378 --> 00:30:23.506
Looks like you're a man down.

368
00:30:23.590 --> 00:30:26.175
Ladies and
gentlemen of the jury.

369
00:30:26.258 --> 00:30:29.095
the defendant has been indicted
for several serious crimes.

370
00:30:29.178 --> 00:30:31.889
But I'm instructing you.
as a point of law...

371
00:30:31.973 --> 00:30:33.933
You know those college stress dreams.

372
00:30:34.016 --> 00:30:36.060
when you show up to your
class in your underwear?

373
00:30:36.143 --> 00:30:37.854
- Yeah?
- That's me right now.

374
00:30:38.855 --> 00:30:41.983
God damn. Matt was supposed
to deliver opening. not me.

375
00:30:42.066 --> 00:30:44.902
Ms. Reyes. are the People ready
to begin opening statements?

376
00:30:44.986 --> 00:30:46.362
More than ready. Your Honor.

377
00:30:47.404 --> 00:30:48.615
Should we be worried?

378
00:30:48.698 --> 00:30:52.076
I mean. there's no way
Matt misses this. right?

379
00:30:52.159 --> 00:30:53.839
Ladies and
gentlemen of the jury...

380
00:30:54.704 --> 00:30:59.125
Frank Castle brutally tortured
and murdered 30 people.

381
00:31:00.334 --> 00:31:02.378
Thirty that we know of.

382
00:31:03.755 --> 00:31:06.382
He took the law into his own hands.

383
00:31:06.466 --> 00:31:12.138
Acted as judge. jury. and...
most violent executioner.

384
00:31:12.221 --> 00:31:17.434
And you will hear that the defendant's
victims were criminals...

385
00:31:17.519 --> 00:31:20.437
but the victims are not
on trial here today.

386
00:31:20.522 --> 00:31:24.066
and justice does not belong in the
hands of a man like Frank Castle.

387
00:31:24.150 --> 00:31:26.360
This isn't the Wild West.

388
00:31:26.443 --> 00:31:30.657
Justice is served here...
in a court of law.

389
00:31:30.740 --> 00:31:32.950
And it is up to each of you

390
00:31:33.034 --> 00:31:36.704
to take back the city from
lawless vigilantes...

391
00:31:37.622 --> 00:31:38.831
like Frank Castle.

392
00:31:45.547 --> 00:31:47.549
This man is no hero.

393
00:31:49.551 --> 00:31:51.010
He's a serial killer.

394
00:31:52.469 --> 00:31:54.972
And he is guilty.

395
00:31:58.392 --> 00:31:59.519
Thank you.

396
00:32:02.188 --> 00:32:05.858
Mr. Nelson. are you prepared
to make your opening statement?

397
00:32:05.942 --> 00:32:08.402
- She's good.
- So are you.

398
00:32:09.403 --> 00:32:10.780
Mr. Nelson?

399
00:32:12.740 --> 00:32:16.911
Mr. Nelson. are you reserving the right
to make your statement at a later time?

400
00:32:25.211 --> 00:32:26.212
Screw it.

401
00:32:27.338 --> 00:32:29.173
Um...

402
00:32:29.256 --> 00:32:32.802
No. Your Honor. um... the
defense is ready to proceed.

403
00:32:38.558 --> 00:32:40.517
Uh. ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

404
00:32:41.769 --> 00:32:44.856
the defendant. Frank Castle. is not...

405
00:32:47.274 --> 00:32:48.525
Sorry.

406
00:32:50.570 --> 00:32:52.739
Um...

407
00:32:53.489 --> 00:32:56.784
Mr. Castle is as much a victim...

408
00:32:59.704 --> 00:33:01.288
No. he's not.

409
00:33:08.630 --> 00:33:11.298
Okay. so...

410
00:33:11.382 --> 00:33:14.761
you're 19... standing in hot sand...

411
00:33:15.511 --> 00:33:17.179
sun burning down...

412
00:33:18.973 --> 00:33:20.099
noise...

413
00:33:20.933 --> 00:33:23.019
yelling. gunfire...

414
00:33:24.520 --> 00:33:26.563
The only thing that you know for sure

415
00:33:26.648 --> 00:33:29.316
is that you're surrounded by
an enemy that wants you dead.

416
00:33:31.068 --> 00:33:33.738
But you do it. You endure it.

417
00:33:33.821 --> 00:33:35.447
Why?

418
00:33:35.531 --> 00:33:38.701
Because you have orders.
And you have a duty.

419
00:33:40.077 --> 00:33:43.164
And also because your
life doesn't end here.

420
00:33:44.331 --> 00:33:47.126
You have people you
love waiting at home.

421
00:33:48.044 --> 00:33:52.173
Because... aside from being
a decorated marine...

422
00:33:52.256 --> 00:33:57.511
the man before you is a good
husband and an excellent father.

423
00:33:59.013 --> 00:34:02.934
Frank Castle returned
from the hell of war

424
00:34:03.017 --> 00:34:05.561
wanting nothing more than
to pick up his life.

425
00:34:06.854 --> 00:34:11.400
But his wife... young son and daughter

426
00:34:11.483 --> 00:34:13.945
were brutally murdered by criminals.

427
00:34:14.028 --> 00:34:17.740
and no one. not the police and...

428
00:34:17.824 --> 00:34:21.744
certainly not the District Attorney
stepped up to make it right.

429
00:34:21.828 --> 00:34:23.830
See. Frank Castle never came home.

430
00:34:23.913 --> 00:34:26.958
He just traded in one
war zone for another.

431
00:34:31.170 --> 00:34:34.548
This trial isn't about vigilantes.

432
00:34:34.631 --> 00:34:37.593
It's about the failure
of the justice system.

433
00:34:37.677 --> 00:34:40.888
And how one man. Frank Castle.
is being used as a pawn

434
00:34:40.972 --> 00:34:43.182
to cover up that system's mistakes.

435
00:34:43.265 --> 00:34:45.935
The prosecution wants blood.

436
00:34:46.018 --> 00:34:48.187
But as the judge just said...

437
00:34:48.270 --> 00:34:52.233
to get it. they have to prove their
case beyond a reasonable doubt.

438
00:34:53.275 --> 00:34:55.277
So all I'm asking of you today...

439
00:34:56.195 --> 00:34:57.780
keep an open mind.

440
00:35:00.199 --> 00:35:02.368
That's all. Your Honor.

441
00:35:06.038 --> 00:35:09.416
That was a pretty thick slice
of bullshit there. counselor.

442
00:35:09.500 --> 00:35:11.168
Prosecution.
call your first witness.

443
00:35:11.252 --> 00:35:12.253
Yes. Your Honor.

444
00:35:12.336 --> 00:35:14.255
- Sorry. guys.
- Where the hell have you been?

445
00:35:14.338 --> 00:35:16.257
Look. I made a mistake. Karen.
I feel terrible about it.

446
00:35:16.340 --> 00:35:17.800
but. Foggy. I caught some
of your opening statement.

447
00:35:17.884 --> 00:35:19.093
- You did great.
- He was amazing.

448
00:35:19.176 --> 00:35:21.428
Hey. hey. thanks for
keeping us afloat. buddy.

449
00:35:22.471 --> 00:35:24.640
Yeah. well...

450
00:35:24.724 --> 00:35:28.144
hopefully Reyes didn't notice
my buckets of flop sweat.

451
00:35:28.227 --> 00:35:30.813
And if the DA's office didn't
suspect we had nothing before.

452
00:35:30.897 --> 00:35:31.898
they gotta be sure now.

453
00:35:31.981 --> 00:35:33.149
Well. then we'll just
have to change that.

454
00:35:33.232 --> 00:35:35.151
Yeah. who's on the prosecution's
witness list for tomorrow?

455
00:35:35.234 --> 00:35:37.694
Uh... I've got it. here.

456
00:35:41.532 --> 00:35:43.117
Tepper. wonderful.

457
00:35:43.200 --> 00:35:45.787
Reyes is calling the
chief medical examiner.

458
00:35:45.870 --> 00:35:47.371
From rocky start to Hail Mary.

459
00:35:47.454 --> 00:35:48.455
Why. what do we know about him?

460
00:35:48.539 --> 00:35:50.833
I showed Frank a copy of his
family's autopsy report.

461
00:35:50.917 --> 00:35:52.709
He claims they're faked. and
Tepper's name is all over them.

462
00:35:52.794 --> 00:35:53.795
Well. that's great. All right.

463
00:35:53.878 --> 00:35:55.712
- So we should get him on the record.
- That's what we said.

464
00:35:55.797 --> 00:35:57.799
Which you would've known had you
shown up to the office at all.

465
00:35:57.882 --> 00:36:00.134
- Let me take lead on it. buddy.
- Like you took the lead this morning?

466
00:36:00.217 --> 00:36:01.969
You've made your point. all right?
Let me try at least.

467
00:36:02.053 --> 00:36:03.054
Let me get a crack at this guy.

468
00:36:03.137 --> 00:36:05.681
Even if we get the false
reports entered into evidence.

469
00:36:05.765 --> 00:36:08.642
and it's a big "if." since they
concern an unrelated crime.

470
00:36:08.725 --> 00:36:11.395
odds are slim that this clown's
gonna incriminate himself.

471
00:36:11.478 --> 00:36:14.273
Unless two brilliant attorneys can
figure out a way to trip him up.

472
00:36:14.356 --> 00:36:17.902
- Exactly.
- You want it? Knock yourself out.

473
00:36:17.985 --> 00:36:21.989
But Tepper ain't talking without a fight.
The DA's pulling his strings.

474
00:36:22.073 --> 00:36:24.909
And he's had plenty of time
to bulletproof his story.

475
00:36:24.992 --> 00:36:28.704
We only have 12 hours to tear it down. I
don't know how we do that by tomorrow.

476
00:36:28.788 --> 00:36:32.208
Because Karen's gonna catch me up.
and we're gonna figure out a way.

477
00:36:33.375 --> 00:36:35.878
Fine. but I'm going back to the office.

478
00:36:35.962 --> 00:36:38.380
'cause I have the rest of
the trial to prep for.

479
00:36:43.469 --> 00:36:45.637
- You let him down. Matt.
- I know. Hey. I know.

480
00:36:45.721 --> 00:36:47.441
But I'm gonna make it up to him.

481
00:36:47.473 --> 00:36:48.753
And I'm gonna make it up to you.

482
00:36:49.558 --> 00:36:50.893
Come on.

483
00:36:50.977 --> 00:36:52.777
<i>You get Tepper thinking
about the real report.</i>

484
00:36:52.812 --> 00:36:54.271
- Mmm-hmm.
- The real truth.

485
00:36:54.355 --> 00:36:57.191
And then when he's disoriented. I
follow up with something like...

486
00:36:57.274 --> 00:36:59.110
"Who had you change the report?"

487
00:36:59.193 --> 00:37:00.694
And even if he says "no
one." it proves...

488
00:37:00.777 --> 00:37:02.196
It proves that the report was changed.

489
00:37:02.279 --> 00:37:03.697
- And that's...
- That's brilliant.

490
00:37:03.780 --> 00:37:06.158
- See? You're a natural.
- Huh.

491
00:37:06.242 --> 00:37:08.119
Well. I keep good company.

492
00:37:08.953 --> 00:37:09.996
Ah. you know what?

493
00:37:10.079 --> 00:37:12.248
Why don't I help you go through
Tepper's bread-crumb questions?

494
00:37:12.331 --> 00:37:14.083
We could. you know. set
'em up. knock 'em down?

495
00:37:14.166 --> 00:37:15.792
All right. but it'll be boring.

496
00:37:15.877 --> 00:37:17.503
And tedious.

497
00:37:18.504 --> 00:37:20.422
- Could take all night.
- Hmm.

498
00:37:20.506 --> 00:37:22.842
Well. I don't mind.

499
00:37:22.925 --> 00:37:25.011
- What?
- You ever consider law school?

500
00:37:25.094 --> 00:37:27.889
Oh. I don't know.

501
00:37:27.972 --> 00:37:30.349
Well. Foggy and I know a lot
of good people at Columbia.

502
00:37:31.642 --> 00:37:34.186
I mean. if it's even something you want.

503
00:37:35.812 --> 00:37:39.275
Just thinking Nelson and Murdock
might be more fun as...

504
00:37:39.358 --> 00:37:41.193
Nelson. Murdock and Page.

505
00:37:42.653 --> 00:37:45.948
You're... you're sweet. Uh...

506
00:37:47.158 --> 00:37:50.536
I don't know. I don't know if law
school's really the right fit for me.

507
00:37:50.619 --> 00:37:51.996
Um...

508
00:37:52.079 --> 00:37:55.499
I guess there's just something
about the rules and the loopholes.

509
00:37:55.582 --> 00:37:59.003
It just feels like the truth
gets lost a little too often.

510
00:37:59.086 --> 00:38:01.286
Well. not every case will be
<i>The People v. Frank Castle.</i>

511
00:38:01.338 --> 00:38:02.423
Right. right.

512
00:38:02.506 --> 00:38:05.717
But. you know. it's not
just this case. It's...

513
00:38:06.928 --> 00:38:09.846
Uh...

514
00:38:11.891 --> 00:38:13.142
What is it?

515
00:38:16.312 --> 00:38:17.438
You know. we...

516
00:38:20.357 --> 00:38:21.483
You ever...

517
00:38:22.526 --> 00:38:24.653
think back to the night we first met?

518
00:38:26.072 --> 00:38:28.449
Yeah. all the time.

519
00:38:31.535 --> 00:38:34.455
While I sat in that police station...

520
00:38:34.538 --> 00:38:35.706
alone.

521
00:38:37.541 --> 00:38:39.335
I was afraid of the whole world.

522
00:38:41.878 --> 00:38:43.339
Well. at least. until...

523
00:38:43.422 --> 00:38:45.342
you and Foggy came into my life and...

524
00:38:46.675 --> 00:38:50.304
You trusted me. You gave me hope.

525
00:38:53.307 --> 00:38:56.936
And then we came back to your place.

526
00:38:57.019 --> 00:38:59.438
I offered you Thai food.

527
00:39:00.439 --> 00:39:01.690
God...

528
00:39:02.774 --> 00:39:05.361
I remember everything about
that night. 'cause it's...

529
00:39:06.362 --> 00:39:08.489
not every day your life is threatened...

530
00:39:09.698 --> 00:39:11.993
then saved by a man in black.

531
00:39:15.079 --> 00:39:16.872
Hey. you...

532
00:39:17.748 --> 00:39:20.042
You believe in what he does?

533
00:39:20.126 --> 00:39:23.379
- You know. the Devil of Hell's Kitchen.
- Mmm-hmm. mmm-hmm. Um...

534
00:39:27.674 --> 00:39:29.010
I. uh...

535
00:39:31.262 --> 00:39:34.473
- What?
- I... believe in the law.

536
00:39:36.183 --> 00:39:39.103
- If that's what you're asking.
- Right. No. but... but...

537
00:39:39.186 --> 00:39:41.022
But what about when the law fails?

538
00:39:41.105 --> 00:39:42.856
Like it did with me.
like it did with Frank.

539
00:39:42.939 --> 00:39:45.026
You know. what are we supposed
to turn to? What should we...

540
00:39:45.109 --> 00:39:47.611
What should we believe
will protect us then?

541
00:39:49.488 --> 00:39:54.035
See. you're asking a Catholic lawyer.

542
00:39:54.118 --> 00:39:55.827
- I. uh... Yes.
- What do you...

543
00:39:55.911 --> 00:39:58.580
- What do you want me to say?
- I don't know.

544
00:39:59.999 --> 00:40:01.542
Uh. I guess it's just...

545
00:40:01.625 --> 00:40:04.378
ever since we took on
Frank's case. like...

546
00:40:04.461 --> 00:40:05.462
I keep...

547
00:40:06.463 --> 00:40:10.009
I keep asking myself if there's
really a difference between...

548
00:40:11.343 --> 00:40:13.804
between someone who saves lives and...

549
00:40:13.887 --> 00:40:17.308
someone who prevents lives from
needing to be saved at all.

550
00:40:17.391 --> 00:40:18.434
Right?

551
00:40:20.477 --> 00:40:21.562
Wait... Wait a second.

552
00:40:21.645 --> 00:40:25.232
Frank Castle should be behind bars.

553
00:40:25.316 --> 00:40:27.776
I mean. he deserves a fair
trial. but he's murdered people.

554
00:40:27.859 --> 00:40:29.320
Yeah. right. Bad people.

555
00:40:29.403 --> 00:40:30.821
I mean. like the ones
who killed his family

556
00:40:30.904 --> 00:40:31.905
or the ones who came after me.

557
00:40:31.988 --> 00:40:34.283
But it's not Frank's
decision who lives or dies.

558
00:40:34.366 --> 00:40:36.452
That's up to God...

559
00:40:36.535 --> 00:40:39.246
or sometimes a jury.

560
00:40:39.330 --> 00:40:41.165
What happened to Frank's
family is a tragedy. Karen.

561
00:40:41.248 --> 00:40:42.666
but it doesn't give him
the right to kill...

562
00:40:42.749 --> 00:40:44.751
No. No. no. no. God... God. no!
Not the right. that's...

563
00:40:44.835 --> 00:40:46.503
That's not what I'm saying.
I'm just saying that...

564
00:40:46.587 --> 00:40:48.130
I can understand why Frank... why...

565
00:40:48.214 --> 00:40:49.923
why anyone would seek vengeance
for something after...

566
00:40:50.006 --> 00:40:51.566
- after losing it...
- Whoa. no. no. no.

567
00:40:51.592 --> 00:40:53.719
That's not the same.
Vengeance is not justice.

568
00:40:53.802 --> 00:40:55.387
What he's doing is completely wrong.

569
00:40:55.471 --> 00:40:57.431
But. right or wrong. you
can't deny that it works.

570
00:41:01.102 --> 00:41:02.311
You really believe that?

571
00:41:02.394 --> 00:41:04.063
I don't know. No.

572
00:41:09.693 --> 00:41:11.027
Maybe.

573
00:41:19.703 --> 00:41:21.372
- Um...
- No. um...

574
00:41:21.455 --> 00:41:23.957
You know. maybe this is a
good time to call it a night.

575
00:41:25.126 --> 00:41:27.544
I just think we're both exhausted. and...

576
00:41:27.628 --> 00:41:29.505
You know. a case this
big. let's just...

577
00:41:29.530 --> 00:41:30.155
Um...

578
00:41:30.214 --> 00:41:31.590
Yes. you're probably right.

579
00:41:33.967 --> 00:41:37.096
I don't know. maybe. uh. after...
after the trial's over.

580
00:41:37.179 --> 00:41:39.515
- Yeah. a real date next time.
- Good.

581
00:41:42.643 --> 00:41:43.644
Thanks.

582
00:41:55.071 --> 00:41:57.073
- Uh. good night.
- Good night. Karen.

583
00:41:59.326 --> 00:42:00.744
Get some rest.

584
00:42:13.340 --> 00:42:17.428
- How long were you listening?
- I wasn't listening.

585
00:42:17.511 --> 00:42:19.138
I didn't hear anything about your work

586
00:42:19.221 --> 00:42:22.599
that would make me want to tie a
noose and test it on my neck.

587
00:42:22.683 --> 00:42:25.186
I won't even mention what I didn't
hear about your girlfriend.

588
00:42:25.269 --> 00:42:28.439
- I warned you not to interrupt my life.
- This is not your life. Matthew.

589
00:42:28.522 --> 00:42:30.732
You may not give a damn about
what I've made for myself.

590
00:42:30.816 --> 00:42:32.609
but that is what's most important to me.

591
00:42:32.693 --> 00:42:35.904
All right? She... is important to me.

592
00:42:36.822 --> 00:42:37.864
Right.

593
00:42:38.990 --> 00:42:40.075
Sorry.

594
00:42:41.702 --> 00:42:45.331
I didn't know your time pairing wine
with Thai food was so important.

595
00:42:45.414 --> 00:42:47.208
What do you want?

596
00:42:47.291 --> 00:42:51.086
I looked more carefully at
Roxxon's construction investment.

597
00:42:51.170 --> 00:42:53.797
Seems there's only a small
number of projects in New York

598
00:42:53.880 --> 00:42:56.049
capable of moving that much dirt.

599
00:42:56.132 --> 00:42:59.345
We pay the sites a visit. I bet
we find out what they're hiding.

600
00:43:00.262 --> 00:43:02.639
- What are these sites?
- Um...

601
00:43:02.723 --> 00:43:06.310
The Conservatory Hotel. the
Midtown Tunnel project.

602
00:43:06.393 --> 00:43:08.812
and some big build
site at 44th and 11th.

603
00:43:08.895 --> 00:43:10.897
44th and 11th.

604
00:43:10.981 --> 00:43:12.524
- You know it?
- Yeah. Midland Circle.

605
00:43:13.192 --> 00:43:14.651
There was a tenement on that block

606
00:43:14.735 --> 00:43:18.239
before Wilson Fisk swallowed it up
in his Better Tomorrow initiative.

607
00:43:18.322 --> 00:43:20.907
- How did the Japanese get hold of it?
- I don't know.

608
00:43:20.991 --> 00:43:24.370
But before I fought Nobu. I found
blueprints at Midland Circle.

609
00:43:25.579 --> 00:43:29.165
Now. I always thought Nobu was just
a weapon Fisk sent to take me out.

610
00:43:29.250 --> 00:43:31.502
that Fisk had interests
tied up in the building.

611
00:43:31.585 --> 00:43:33.003
but maybe he didn't want it at all.

612
00:43:33.086 --> 00:43:36.215
I mean. what if he only acquired
Midland Circle for the Japanese?

613
00:43:36.298 --> 00:43:38.133
That's a curious riddle.

614
00:43:38.217 --> 00:43:39.968
one I think we should
go and solve together.

615
00:43:40.051 --> 00:43:41.262
Elektra. I got court in the morning.

616
00:43:41.345 --> 00:43:43.972
- I got a case to prepare. I got...
- Tomorrow night. then.

617
00:43:48.143 --> 00:43:49.770
Cheap wine.

618
00:43:49.853 --> 00:43:52.356
Finish your homework.
I'll do some recon.

619
00:43:55.901 --> 00:43:58.320
And so. Dr. Tepper.
the medical examiner's office

620
00:43:58.404 --> 00:44:01.865
can confirm that the 15 victims
found at the Irish Social Club

621
00:44:01.948 --> 00:44:03.534
all died of multiple gunshot wounds.

622
00:44:03.617 --> 00:44:05.661
Yes. that's correct.

623
00:44:05.744 --> 00:44:11.166
Um. all 15 victims died of wounds
inflicted by the same caliber bullet...

624
00:44:11.250 --> 00:44:13.669
each shot multiple times.

625
00:44:14.461 --> 00:44:15.462
Thank you.

626
00:44:16.463 --> 00:44:17.506
Your witness.

627
00:44:23.219 --> 00:44:26.014
- Cross your fingers.
- I'm crossing everything.

628
00:44:37.276 --> 00:44:38.985
Dr. Gregory Tepper.

629
00:44:39.069 --> 00:44:41.655
how long have you been medical
examiner for the city of New York?

630
00:44:41.738 --> 00:44:44.115
Uh. 14 years. uh. give or take.

631
00:44:44.199 --> 00:44:47.077
And how many death certificates would you
estimate you've signed in that time?

632
00:44:47.160 --> 00:44:48.161
Huh?

633
00:44:49.287 --> 00:44:51.748
Um. I don't. uh...

634
00:44:51.832 --> 00:44:52.958
It's probably in the tens of thousands.

635
00:44:53.041 --> 00:44:55.168
Objection. Your Honor.
leading the witness...

636
00:44:55.251 --> 00:44:57.629
- I'm not sure where.
- Mr. Murdock...

637
00:44:57.713 --> 00:44:59.423
I have something I need to say.

638
00:45:00.173 --> 00:45:02.551
- Doctor?
- Your Honor. I'm sorry. but...

639
00:45:02.634 --> 00:45:04.386
I have to. on the record...

640
00:45:05.554 --> 00:45:07.639
I need to say something
about what I did.

641
00:45:10.016 --> 00:45:12.436
- Clear the gallery.
- Yes. Your Honor.

642
00:45:12.519 --> 00:45:16.314
All jury members. please exit
back to the deliberation room.

643
00:45:17.148 --> 00:45:18.442
Everyone in the gallery.

644
00:45:18.525 --> 00:45:21.695
please make your way out of
the courtroom at this time.

645
00:45:26.950 --> 00:45:28.190
What's all this about?

646
00:45:29.202 --> 00:45:30.537
I...

647
00:45:30.621 --> 00:45:34.708
I know what the defense was gonna
ask me about. and it's true.

648
00:45:34.791 --> 00:45:36.668
I altered the autopsy reports.

649
00:45:36.752 --> 00:45:38.545
Uh. you're referring to
the official findings

650
00:45:38.629 --> 00:45:40.229
on the murders of Frank Castle's family?

651
00:45:40.255 --> 00:45:42.173
Not just them.

652
00:45:42.257 --> 00:45:44.342
You don't understand. I had to do it.

653
00:45:44.426 --> 00:45:48.472
- Those animals came to my office.
- Who came to your office?

654
00:45:49.055 --> 00:45:51.055
After the defendant's
family was murdered.

655
00:45:51.099 --> 00:45:53.018
two men I'd never seen before...

656
00:45:53.101 --> 00:45:56.187
they warned me. if I didn't
fix the case reports.

657
00:45:56.271 --> 00:45:58.690
they'd come after my family next.

658
00:45:58.774 --> 00:46:02.360
You falsified the autopsy
findings on the Castle family?

659
00:46:03.028 --> 00:46:04.905
Them and one more.

660
00:46:04.988 --> 00:46:06.823
- Who?
- I don't know.

661
00:46:06.907 --> 00:46:08.909
Some John Doe killed the same day.

662
00:46:08.992 --> 00:46:11.286
Male. adult. multiple gunshot wounds.

663
00:46:11.369 --> 00:46:14.623
Look. you can fire me. arrest me...
I don't care.

664
00:46:14.706 --> 00:46:18.209
I thought this was behind
me. but after last night...

665
00:46:18.293 --> 00:46:20.712
Doctor. did something happen last
night to impact your testimony?

666
00:46:20.796 --> 00:46:23.131
She was in my house.

667
00:46:23.214 --> 00:46:24.466
She tied me up.

668
00:46:25.592 --> 00:46:29.054
She said she didn't give a
damn who got to me before.

669
00:46:29.137 --> 00:46:31.765
If I didn't tell the defense
what really happened.

670
00:46:31.848 --> 00:46:33.434
she'd hunt me down and kill me.

671
00:46:33.517 --> 00:46:35.519
- Who told you this?
- I don't know.

672
00:46:36.478 --> 00:46:37.479
A woman.

673
00:46:37.563 --> 00:46:40.524
Her face was covered. Had
some foreign accent.

674
00:46:40.607 --> 00:46:43.485
Your Honor. I believe the defense
intends to distract the jury

675
00:46:43.569 --> 00:46:47.072
and make this case about some
impossible-to-prove conspiracy theories...

676
00:46:47.155 --> 00:46:48.156
Impossible to prove?

677
00:46:48.239 --> 00:46:50.451
Your ME just confirmed that he
doctored the autopsy records.

678
00:46:50.534 --> 00:46:52.285
He also said that he'd been threatened.

679
00:46:52.368 --> 00:46:55.371
If my office finds out that your
firm had anything to do with this...

680
00:46:55.456 --> 00:46:58.459
Our firm? For all we know. it
was you who sent those goons.

681
00:46:58.542 --> 00:46:59.668
I've heard enough.

682
00:46:59.751 --> 00:47:03.505
It's clear to me that whatever Dr. Tepper
may know about these autopsy reports

683
00:47:03.589 --> 00:47:05.006
has been tainted

684
00:47:05.090 --> 00:47:08.218
by threats made by person
or persons unknown.

685
00:47:08.301 --> 00:47:09.928
Then the defense asks for a mistrial.

686
00:47:10.011 --> 00:47:13.139
Not on your life. Mr. Nelson. I'm
still not convinced these documents.

687
00:47:13.223 --> 00:47:15.809
whatever they may be. are
even relevant to this trial.

688
00:47:15.892 --> 00:47:18.937
I'm striking the doctor's
entire testimony

689
00:47:19.020 --> 00:47:21.857
and instructing the jurors to disregard
anything they may have heard.

690
00:47:21.940 --> 00:47:24.568
- Your Honor. I strongly urge you to...
- We're done here. counselor.

691
00:47:24.651 --> 00:47:27.738
Trial will reconvene tomorrow with
the prosecution's next witness.

692
00:47:29.656 --> 00:47:31.366
Once again. Reyes finds
a new way to screw us.

693
00:47:31.449 --> 00:47:33.769
You'd think it'd get easier.
but somehow it's more painful.

694
00:47:33.827 --> 00:47:36.538
Foggy. Foggy... it wasn't Reyes.

695
00:47:37.539 --> 00:47:40.000
- What?
- The woman who threatened Tepper.

696
00:47:41.710 --> 00:47:42.878
It was Elektra.

697
00:47:44.170 --> 00:47:46.172
From college.

698
00:47:46.256 --> 00:47:48.424
- Elektra?
- Yeah. she's back in town.

699
00:47:49.801 --> 00:47:51.386
- Your ex-girlfriend?
- Yes.

700
00:47:51.469 --> 00:47:54.222
No. This is insane.

701
00:47:54.305 --> 00:47:57.559
She's a diplomat's daughter. a...
a debutante.

702
00:47:57.643 --> 00:48:00.061
Not anymore. She's. uh...

703
00:48:01.479 --> 00:48:03.690
She's... she's different. She's...
she's dangerous.

704
00:48:03.774 --> 00:48:06.234
Yeah. no shit. She
nearly got you expelled.

705
00:48:06.317 --> 00:48:09.571
I mean. she screwed your semester
of torts. civil procedure...

706
00:48:09.655 --> 00:48:12.365
You almost missed the final
because she hurt you so bad.

707
00:48:12.448 --> 00:48:13.491
And now. what?

708
00:48:13.575 --> 00:48:15.994
- She's... breaking into an ME's house?
- Okay.

709
00:48:16.077 --> 00:48:17.871
So. the Yakuza
didn't go away. all right?

710
00:48:17.954 --> 00:48:18.997
They're still here in Hell's Kitchen.

711
00:48:19.080 --> 00:48:21.457
Elektra is trying to help me
stop them. infiltrating...

712
00:48:21.542 --> 00:48:22.918
What are you even talking about?

713
00:48:23.001 --> 00:48:24.753
She was going up against
them by herself. and she...

714
00:48:24.836 --> 00:48:27.255
- Your ex-girlfriend?
- Yeah. I'm trying to protect the city...

715
00:48:27.338 --> 00:48:31.384
I knew she was crazy. I didn't
know that she was homicidal.

716
00:48:31.467 --> 00:48:33.344
She's. um...

717
00:48:34.638 --> 00:48:36.097
my new client.

718
00:48:37.432 --> 00:48:39.976
Foggy. the. uh... rich one.

719
00:48:40.060 --> 00:48:41.311
The private one.

720
00:48:44.272 --> 00:48:46.149
- You lied again.
- I did. I lied.

721
00:48:46.232 --> 00:48:47.984
but. look. the Yakuza are
funneling money into something

722
00:48:48.068 --> 00:48:49.611
even bigger and darker
than before. all right?

723
00:48:49.695 --> 00:48:51.237
Elektra came to me. I'm
trying to help her...

724
00:48:51.321 --> 00:48:53.907
You wanted to take this trial!

725
00:48:53.990 --> 00:48:56.326
You missed
strategy sessions...

726
00:48:56.409 --> 00:48:59.871
witness prep. opening statements.
and you criminally decimate...

727
00:48:59.955 --> 00:49:00.956
No. I didn't. She...

728
00:49:01.039 --> 00:49:02.874
I never told her anything
about the trial. all right?

729
00:49:02.958 --> 00:49:05.711
The one witness that could've
helped us do what I wanted to do.

730
00:49:05.794 --> 00:49:06.795
which is take down Reyes!

731
00:49:06.878 --> 00:49:09.422
She must've overheard me talking to
Karen. and then she moved on her own.

732
00:49:09.505 --> 00:49:11.049
I would... I didn't
sanction. I would never...

733
00:49:11.132 --> 00:49:13.844
- I don't care! I don't care. Matt!
- I'm furious with her!

734
00:49:13.927 --> 00:49:16.137
Stop acting like these
things just happen to you!

735
00:49:16.221 --> 00:49:18.932
No one's making you go out all hours
of the night fighting bad guys

736
00:49:19.015 --> 00:49:23.019
and nobody makes you lie to your
friends. over and over again!

737
00:49:24.605 --> 00:49:26.940
Elektra is not the problem. Matt.

738
00:49:29.693 --> 00:49:30.777
You are.

739
00:49:33.614 --> 00:49:34.698
It's almost dark.

740
00:49:34.781 --> 00:49:36.992
- I'm sure there's someplace you gotta be...
- You're not walking away.

741
00:49:37.075 --> 00:49:38.785
- No. 'cause you know what?
- Don't walk away from me. Foggy.

742
00:49:38.869 --> 00:49:42.538
If the last few days are any indication.
you sure as hell haven't been here!

743
00:49:45.500 --> 00:49:48.712
Going forward. I will count
on you for nothing at all.

744
00:49:53.133 --> 00:49:55.260
Tell your girlfriend to
stay away from my trial.

745
00:49:55.343 --> 00:49:57.183
Yeah. she's not... Elektra's
not my girlfriend.

746
00:49:57.220 --> 00:49:59.514
Then you should be the one
to tell Karen about her.

747
00:50:03.351 --> 00:50:04.602
Hey.

748
00:50:04.686 --> 00:50:07.648
- Hey. I heard yelling.
- Yeah. you should talk to Matt about it.

749
00:50:07.731 --> 00:50:08.732
Foggy!

750
00:50:11.442 --> 00:50:12.986
- Hey. what the hell happened in there?
- We're fine.

751
00:50:13.069 --> 00:50:15.155
No. no. no. you don't treat me
like I'm just your secretary.

752
00:50:15.238 --> 00:50:16.489
I've done more work on
this case than you have!

753
00:50:16.572 --> 00:50:19.409
- I can't get into this right now. Karen.
- No. enough of the dodgy bullshit.

754
00:50:19.492 --> 00:50:21.036
I deserve to know what is
going on with you two.

755
00:50:21.119 --> 00:50:22.120
With you.

756
00:50:23.121 --> 00:50:25.581
You asking as my co-worker?

757
00:50:25.666 --> 00:50:28.501
Or my girlfriend?

758
00:50:29.419 --> 00:50:31.171
- Both.
- Yeah.

759
00:50:31.254 --> 00:50:32.630
I am sorry you're caught
in the middle of this.

760
00:50:32.714 --> 00:50:34.549
but right now. I have to go.

761
00:50:34.632 --> 00:50:37.260
- Where?
- I'll see you tomorrow. Karen.

762
00:50:40.055 --> 00:50:42.140
Yeah. maybe.

763
00:50:58.114 --> 00:51:02.243
What the hell did you do?
I told you to stay out of my life.

764
00:51:02.327 --> 00:51:04.370
I never asked you to coerce a witness!

765
00:51:04.454 --> 00:51:06.622
- You had a problem. so I stepped in.
- No! It doesn't help.

766
00:51:06.707 --> 00:51:09.334
We can't even use his testimony because
of you. It was all thrown out.

767
00:51:09.417 --> 00:51:11.294
I was only following your rules.

768
00:51:12.337 --> 00:51:14.965
- What rules?
- You don't get what you want by day.

769
00:51:15.048 --> 00:51:17.968
You take it by force at night.

770
00:51:18.051 --> 00:51:20.095
This is who you are. Matthew.

771
00:51:21.429 --> 00:51:24.182
And don't fool yourself into
thinking it's anything else.

772
00:51:24.265 --> 00:51:26.309
What I do...

773
00:51:26.392 --> 00:51:28.019
is none of your business.

774
00:51:28.895 --> 00:51:32.190
- Both halves of my life are mine.
- Fine.

775
00:51:33.608 --> 00:51:36.194
I'll stay out of your boring legal shit.

776
00:51:37.821 --> 00:51:39.990
Now. you wanna fight me?

777
00:51:40.073 --> 00:51:42.993
Or you wanna fight the guys who
are tearing your city apart?

778
00:52:52.728 --> 00:52:55.773
- You didn't wanna help?
- You didn't want me to.

779
00:52:58.276 --> 00:52:59.277
Ready?

780
00:53:09.955 --> 00:53:11.122
You hear something?

781
00:53:12.999 --> 00:53:15.668
We're alone.

782
00:53:39.484 --> 00:53:42.737
It's empty. There's nothing in here.

783
00:53:42.820 --> 00:53:46.449
- The Yakuza were guarding something.
- Yeah. but...

784
00:53:53.706 --> 00:53:54.707
Shh!

785
00:53:55.625 --> 00:53:57.878
- Elektra.
- What?

786
00:54:00.964 --> 00:54:02.604
You're not
gonna believe this.

787
00:54:17.063 --> 00:54:18.148
Holy shit.

788
00:54:22.402 --> 00:54:25.196
Why are the
Yakuza digging a hole?

789
00:54:27.698 --> 00:54:29.159
Give me the flashlight.

790
00:54:40.628 --> 00:54:43.965
- Did it hit the bottom?
- No.

791
00:54:45.133 --> 00:54:47.302
Tell me when it does.

792
00:54:48.305 --> 00:55:48.637
